{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:40:15.547663+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "I have enough information from the `Pipfile`. Here's a summary of the **main Python dependency and service stack** used by this FastAPI template:\n\n---\n\n## Core Framework\n- **FastAPI** (with all extras) — the main web framework\n\n## Database Stack\n- **PostgreSQL** as the database\n  - `psycopg2` — synchronous PostgreSQL adapter\n  - `asyncpg` — async PostgreSQL driver\n  - `databases[postgresql]` — async database abstraction layer\n  - `sqlalchemy-utils` — SQLAlchemy utility helpers\n  - **Alembic** — database migration tool\n\n## Auth / Security Libraries\n- **`python-jose[cryptography]`** — JWT token creation and verification\n- **`passlib[bcrypt]`** — password hashing with bcrypt\n\n## Redis Support\n- **`aioredis`** — async Redis client for caching/pub-sub/etc.\n\n## Other Notable Dependencies\n- **`python-multipart`** — form/file upload support (needed by FastAPI for form data)\n- **`pytest`** — testing framework\n\n---\n\n### Service Stack Summary\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|---|---|\n| **Web Framework** | FastAPI |\n| **Database** | PostgreSQL (via psycopg2 + asyncpg + databases) |\n| **Migrations** | Alembic |\n| **Auth (JWT)** | python-jose |\n| **Auth (Passwords)** | passlib + bcrypt |\n| **Cache / Queue** | Redis (via aioredis) |\n| **Containerization** | Docker + docker-compose |\n\nThis is a fairly standard modern Python async stack: **FastAPI + PostgreSQL + Redis**, with **JWT-based authentication** and **Alembic-managed migrations**.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 576, "prompt_tokens": 3420, "total_tokens": 3996, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 210, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 3136, "cache_write_tokens": 0